modStarterQuestWelcome:
{#ba9999:If you're new to Wayward, this //Starter Quest// can help you survive by teaching you the basics. This optional walkthrough will take approximately 20-40 minutes.}

Press {Bindings:DialogQuests} to toggle this dialog.

Click "//Complete Quest//" to start the quest line.

modStarterQuestGearUp:
{#ba9999:Attacking creatures and auto-gathering from the terrain uses your equipment. Let's equip an item now.}

1. Open your equipment {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Interface):dialog} with {Bindings:DialogEquipment} or click the equipment icon at the top of the screen.

2. Equip a tool or weapon by dragging it from your inventory to the equipment slot of your choice.

Alternatively, you can press {Bindings:GameItemEquipToggle} while hovering over an item to toggle it equipped.

{link(Menu.HelpArticle.HeldItems):Learn more about Held Items}

modStarterQuestQuickslots:
{#ba9999:All items have a list of actions that can be performed on them at any time.}

Use {Bindings:GameItemMenu} to open an item's action menu.

{#ba9999:Using actions in this way can be cumbersome. To bind an item's action to a single keypress, you can use Quickslots.}

- Drag and drop an item into a quickslot.

- OR use the "//Add to Quickslot//" action on the item.

- OR use one of the "Quickslot Toggle" bindings on an item, such as {Bindings:GameQuickSlotToggle1}, {Bindings:GameQuickSlotToggle2}, or {Bindings:GameQuickSlotToggle3}.

{#ba9999:Once the item is in the quickslot, it can be used with its respective binding, which is listed underneath the quickslot.}

You can change which action it executes by using {Bindings:GameItemMenu} on the quicklot and clicking the "x" next to the action of your choice.
